F0000>(8/21/01 2:22:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.megamanmush.mudservices.com/files/masters/bassCD.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What evil is (long)</span><hr size=1> I'm going to point straight out that these are just my opinions on the subject. You can take them as you like. I'm going to try not to flame anyone, and would appriciate it if I got some thoughtful responses and the thread didn't degenerate into a flame war. Warning, this is going to be long.<br>
<br>
I like to RP, and am in an RP guild. I've RPed exclusively evil characters on various MUSHes for the last 3 years straight. I still do. Back during the server beta, I played an iksar shaman up to level 7. When the server was wiped, I started a DE cleric, and played him up until level 10 in those days where it was tough to find anything to kill. Then I went through a period where my computer was down, and I didn't have any means to play. I recently got my computer running again, and figured out that I was a little bored with EQ. I didn't log on at all for a week or so. I figured out why I was bored with SZ. It didn't feel any different than playing on Lanys. Neutrals invaded EC occasionally, but I can probably count on one hand how many I saw over level 6. The only good (presumably) I ever saw was the high elf corpse that lay outside Neriak. So when I got back I deleted my DE cleric and made a good cleric. So I have played both sides (apologies to all those newts out there).<br>
<br>
But what somewhat bothers me are those who actively go out and gank newbies, and the ones who make the excuse for them that 'They're evil, that's what evil does.'  It's said in fiction that the measure of great heroes are great villians, and I believe the opposite to be true as well. Great villians don't go out and spend all their time knocking over orphanages and stealing candy from babies. That's what they have underlings for. Sure, they might kill a 'lowbie' that crosses their path every now and then, but all the time? Did Kitiara Uth Matar or Raistlin Majere go out of their way to personally flatten every kender in Kenderhome? Was Professor Moriarty personally sneaking around London cutting the throats of children? Did Megatron personally wade into schoolyards every day and start blasting buildings and stepping on kids? Did the Joker personally spend all his time flattening orphanages? No. All these great villians either viewed that stuff as a waste of time, or let underlings do the job for them. They had better things to do. More evil goals to accomplish. They even *gasp* plotted against the heroes who were their equals, made and carried out great plans of selfishness and destruction that we all love to read and watch. <br>
<br>
Now we have some of the evils here on Sullon. I'm talking about the ones who spend 90% of their time griefing others that have no hope of fighting back. What does that say about a certain person we all know who hangs around Crushbone and who's stated goal is to see how many people he can make quit? He might be 'evil' but there's a difference between an admirable great villian and an underling common street punk more worthy of contempt than admiration. I don't think I have to state what catigory I think these people fall into.<br>
<br>
Once again, thoughtful opinions are welcome. <p>Hesster Shadowscale<br>
Knight of Scale<br>
Lanys T'vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/ugravedirt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gravedirt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Message Board Warrior</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 2:48:06 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.thegeekhost.com/gravedirt/GDsmaller.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What evil is (long)</span><hr size=1> Each combatant in the war has their part to play, and he's doing his part well. <br>
