</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/bsullonzektavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=slooth>slooth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 3:23:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What evil is (long)</span><hr size=1> If it bothers you so much , then get your wonderfull team to run him out. When newts start trying to have big balls in WC Evils port in from Kunark , while a few rally togther in closer zones to puch them back deep into Kith. Run him out instead of bitching about what he is doing .... whats wrong dont have any high lvl's on your team able to go in and rid you of the nuisance ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uwazu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wazu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 3:43:19 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://faceweb-004.facelink.com/edit/raw/rawimage/86/2144586.jpg height = 100 length = 100?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What evil is (long)</span><hr size=1> Hesster -<br>
<br>
A lot of arch-villains target masses of innocent and helpless civilians.  It may not be orphanages, but if you do something like plant a nuclear bomb in the middle of a large city then you're victims are basically a large mass of helpless people.  (Like in the first Batman movie when Joker was going to release poison gas on the city of Gotham.)<br>
<br>
It's usually the heroes that have to come to the rescue of the masses of helpless civilians and foil the villain's plan.  From that perspective, I think Kronar is playing a villain very well, whether he means to or not. <p><font face=Verdana><Font Size = 1><B>If you define cowardice as running away at the first sign of danger, screaming and tripping and begging for mercy, then yes, Mr. Brave man, I guess I'm a coward.
</B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uhesster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hesster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 5:02:55 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.megamanmush.mudservices.com/files/masters/bassCD.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What evil is (long)</span><hr size=1> Wazu &amp; Gravedirt: Evil they might be, but they're not villians, or at least, not ones worth noticing. I guess I'm just more of an idealist than anything.<br>
<br>
As for Slooth: I have no idea how many high level goods there are on this server or who they might be. I'm not even sure what the highest level in my own guild is. Everyone is /anon or /roleplay, and  when you're the underdog team, you don't go running around hostile territory (and almost all of it is hostile to us) /shouting &quot;Level 52 good warrior LFG!&quot; <br>
<br>
This was more of a philosophical rant, really. That being said, the goods will not be low level forever. When we get high enough, we will take care of the problem. I myself am looking forward to the day when I can be part of a group that kicks Kronar's bony erudite ass all the way back to Odus, and I'm sure many of the newbies he's been ganking in Crushbone and Butcherblock are whetting their blades as well. But for now, my guild is arranging a raid into evil territory for sometime in the near future, in which I will take part. So we are doing things proactively as well. <p>Hesster Shadowscale<br>
Knight of Scale<br>
Lanys T'vyl</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=FAEBD7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/umcbudsmoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>McBudSmoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 5:09:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What evil is (long)</span><hr size=1> well the difference is those are all villains from actual stories, theres rl people playing these chars an rl people like to do what the fuck they want. <br>
<br>
Plus it seems like your implying only evils gank lowbies, whats the excuse for all the newtz an goods that have done the same? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub73.ezboard.com/uhesster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hesster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>poon</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/21/01 5:35:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.megamanmush.mudservices.com/files/masters/bassCD.gif height=110 width=68></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What evil is (long)</span><hr size=1> Then don't try and excuse it by saying 'We're evil, what do you expect?'. I'm actually more annoyed by those that try and cover up their actions by making lame excuses that they're evil.<br>
<br>
As for neuts and goods ganking lowbies, I'm sure it goes on, but not to the scale that certain evils do it. I don't see the other teams racking up massive negative points. At least in this regard, the point system doesn't lie. Evils are doing much more ganking of lowbies than goods or neuts.<br>
<br>
Have I been PKd by too many reds? Probably. When Kronar and his friends come to play in Crushbone, I don't piss and moan and call them names, I simply leave and find somewhere else to get exp or go match up against evils my own level. But one day he'll feel my mace cracking the back of his skull, and that day will be sweet justice indeed... <p>Hesster Shadowscale<br>
